author: AbdelMonaem AbdAllah

text:
yes, you can use absolute imports.
So let's say if you have directory structure as below: 
dir/pkg1/module1.py
dir/pkg1/pkg2/module2.py

if you want to import module2.py inside module1.py then you can just use the statement as below:
from pkg2 import module2

However, if your directory structure is like:
dir/pkg1/module1.py
dir/pkg2/module2.py

then in order to import module2 inside your module1, you need to make sure that your parent directory is included in the PYTHONPATH environment variable.

Hope this helps...
